hout-africa.com/entertainment/ghana-4x4-%e2%80%9cfresh-one%e2%80%9d-tops-at-4syte-tv-music-video-awards-2010/|archive-date=15 July 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|Best Storyline Video\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|Best Female Video\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|Best African Act Video\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|Ghana Music Awards\n|Highlife Song of the Year\n|rowspan=\"2\"|\"Daa Ke Daa\"\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"GhanaNewsNow.com\">{{cite web|title=Ghana Music Awards nominees out, Sarkodie leads the pack|url=http://www.ghananewsnow.com/2010/03/02/ghana-music-awards-nominees-out-sarkodie-leads-the-pack/|publisher=GhanaNewsNow.com|accessdate=10 July 2014|date=2 March 2010}}</ref>\n|-\n|Record of the Year\n|{{won}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|<ref>{{cite web|last1=Mensah|first1=Nii|title=Ghana Music Awards 2010 winners|url=http://www.ghanamusic.com/news/top-stories/ghana-music-awards-2010-winners/index.html|publisher=Ghana Music.com|accessdate=10 July 2014|date=11 April 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414101443/http://www.ghanamusic.com/news/top-stories/ghana-music-awards-2010-winners/index.html|archivedate=14 April 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|Best Female Vocal Performance\n|rowspan=\"6\"|Herself\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Artist of the Year\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"GhanaNewsNow.com\"/>\n|-\n|[[Kora Awards]]\n|Best African Prospect Award \n|{{won}}\n|<ref name=\"ghanameets\">{{cite web|title=Becca nominated for award in Nigeria|url=http://ghanameets.weebly.com/becca-nominated-for-award-in-nigeria.html|website=ghanameets.weebly.com|accessdate=5 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714163319/http://ghanameets.weebly.com/becca-nominated-for-award-in-nigeria.html|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"8\"|2008\n|rowspan=\"6\"|Ghana Music Awards\n|Artiste of the Year\n|{{nom}}\n|rowspan=\"5\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=Ghana Music Awards 2008: Nominees|url=http://www.ghanabase.com/news/2008/2096.asp|publisher=Ghana Base|accessdate=7 July 2014|date=21 March 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714135135/http://www.ghanabase.com/news/2008/2096.asp|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|Discovery of the Year\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|Best Female Vocal Performance\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|Pop Song of the Year\n|rowspan=\"2\"|\"You Lied to Me\" <br><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(featuring Kwabena Kwabena)</span> \n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|Best Collaboration of the Year\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|Record of the Year\n|''Sugar'' \n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|last1=Debrah|first1=Ameyaw|title=\u2018Madman\u2019 Sweeps Ghana Music Awards|url=http://www.modernghana.com/music/6862/3/madman-sweeps-ghana-music-awards.html|publisher=Modern Ghana|accessdate=7 July 2014|date=30 April 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141024110059/http://www.modernghana.com/music/6862/3/madman-sweeps-ghana-music-awards.html|archive-date=24 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Kora Awards]] {{efn|group=upper-alpha|The 2008 Kora Awards took place on 11 April 2009. It was postponed to improve its delivery.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Awards ceremony Kora Awards 2008 will take place in April 2009|url=http://www.francomix.com/breve-La_ceremonie_des_Trophees_Kora_Awards_2008_se_deroulera_en_avril_2009-755.html|publisher=Franco Mix|accessdate=5 July 2014|date=24 November 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141205141957/http://www.francomix.com/breve-La_ceremonie_des_Trophees_Kora_Awards_2008_se_deroulera_en_avril_2009-755.html|archive-date=5 December 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n|Best Artist or Group Hope \n|rowspan=\"2\"|Herself\n|rowspan=\"2\" {{nom}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=The appointed Kora awards 2008 African music|url=http://www.francomix.com/breve-Les_nommes_aux_Kora_awards_2008_de_la_musique_africaine-700.html|publisher=Franco Mix|accessdate=5 July 2014|date=15 November 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129181742/http://www.francomix.com/breve-Les_nommes_aux_Kora_awards_2008_de_la_musique_africaine-700.html|archive-date=29 November 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|Best Artist or Group of West Africa \n|-\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist-ua}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Ghanaian musicians]]\n*[[List of Ghanaians]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Becca (Ghanaian singer)}}\n*{{Twitter}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Becca}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian female singers]]\n[[Category:People from Kumasi]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Croydon College]]\n[[Category:People educated at Wesley Girls' Senior High School]]\n[[Category:21st-century Ghanaian singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century women singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Becca\n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = Becca in Brazil.jpg\n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt              = \n| caption          = Becca performing at the Meet Ghana hub in [[Natal, Rio Grande do Norte|Natal]] during the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]].\n| native_name      = \n| native_name_lang = \n| birth_name       = Rebecca Akosua Acheampomaa Acheampong\n| alias            = \n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1984|08|15|df=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[Kumasi]], Ghana\n| origin           = [[Accra]], Ghana\n| death_date       = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} (death date 1st) -->\n| death_place      = \n| genre            = {{hlist|[[African popular music|Afropop]]|[[R&B]]|[[highlife]]}}\n| occupation       = {{hlist|Singer|songwriter|actress }}\n| instrument       = Vocals\n| years_active     = 2007\u2014present\n| label            = Zylofon Media<ref>{{cite web |author1=Daniella Adu Asare |title=I want to grow with new management, Zylofon Media \u2013 Becca |url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/entertainment/2017/June-10th/i-want-to-grow-with-new-management-zylofon-media-becca.php |publisher=My Joy Online |accessdate=19 February 2019 |date=10 June 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190905124049/https://www.myjoyonline.com/entertainment/2017/june-10th/i-want-to-grow-with-new-management-zylofon-media-becca.php |archive-date=5 September 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| associated_acts  = {{flatlist|\n*[[Hugh Masekela]]\n*Kwabena Kwabena\n*[[M.I Abaga|MI]]\n*[[2face Idibia]]\n*[[Patoranking]]\n*Jay Storm\n*[[King Ayisoba]]\n*[[Trigmatic]] \n*[[Akwaboah Jnr|Akwaboah]]\n*Uhuru|Uhuru_(band)}}\n| website          = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n}}\n\n'''Rebecca Akosua Acheampomaa Acheampong''' (born 15 August 1984),<ref name=\"Peacefmonline.com \">{{cite web | url=http://people.peacefmonline.com/pages/musicians/becca/biography/ | title=Becca Biography | publisher=Peacefmonline.com | accessdate=17 June 2014 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160630151914/http://people.peacefmonline.com/pages/musicians/becca/biography/ | archive-date=30 June 2016 | url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"Modern Ghana 1\">{{cite web|title=Becca releases \"Sugar\" album|url=http://www.modernghana.com/music/5265/3/becca-releases-sugar-album.html|work=Daily Guide|accessdate=6 July 2014|date=27 August 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203205545/http://www.modernghana.com/music/5265/3/becca-releases-sugar-album.html|archive-date=3 December 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> known [[:wikt:mononym|mononymously]] as '''Becca''', is a [[Ghanaian people|Ghanaian]] singer, songwriter and actress. She first gained recognition as a contestant on the second season of [[TV3 Ghana|TV3]]'s annual singing competition ''Mentor''.<ref name=\"Ghanacelebrities.com\"/> Her debut studio album ''Sugar'' was released in 2007; it earned her five nominations at the 2008 [[Ghana Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ghanabase.com/news/2008/2096.asp | title=Ghana Music Awards 2008: Nominees | publisher=Ghanabase.com | date=21 March 2008 | accessdate=17 June 2014 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714135135/http://www.ghanabase.com/news/2008/2096.asp | archive-date=14 July 2014 | url-status=live }}</ref> The album's lead single \"You Lied to Me\" won Record of the Year at the aforementioned awards show.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.modernghana.com/music/6862/3/madman-sweeps-ghana-music-awards.html | title=\u2018Madman\u2019 Sweeps Ghana Music Awards | publisher=Modern Ghana | date=30 April 2008 | accessdate=17 June 2014 | author=[[Ameyaw Debrah]] | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141024110059/http://www.modernghana.com/music/6862/3/madman-sweeps-ghana-music-awards.html | archive-date=24 October 2014 | url-status=live }}</ref> Becca released her second studio album ''Time 4 Me'' on 16 May 2013. It features guest appearances from [[2face Idibia]], [[M.I Abaga|MI]], [[King Ayisoba]], [[Trigmatic]], Jay Storm and [[Akwaboah Jnr|Akwaboah]]. The album was certified 2x platinum in Ghana. Becca's accolades include one [[Kora Award]], one National Youth Achievers Award, four [[Ghana Music Awards]], and three 4Syte TV Music Video Awards.<ref name=\"Ghanacelebrities.com\">{{cite web | url=http://www.ghanacelebrities.com/celebs/becca/ | title=Becca | publisher=Ghanacelebrities.com | accessdate=17 June 2014 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714192527/http://www.ghanacelebrities.com/celebs/becca/ | archive-date=14 July 2014 | url-status=live }}</ref> In 2013, she headlined the annual Girl Talk concert, which started in 2011.<ref name=\"The Chronicle\">{{cite web|title=Becca's \u2018Girl Talk\u2019 Concert @ National Theatre|url=http://thechronicle.com.gh/beccas-girl-talk-concert-national-theatre/|work=The Chronicle|date=6 December 2013|access-date=7 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714144340/http://thechronicle.com.gh/beccas-girl-talk-concert-national-theatre/|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> Becca was ranked 94 on [[E.tv Ghana]]'s 2013 list of the 100 most influential people in Ghana.<ref>{{cite web|title=e.tv Ghana holds maiden edition of Ghana's Most Influential Awards|url=http://www.etvghana.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=3634:etv-ghana-holds-maiden-edition-of-ghanas-most-influential-awards&catid=96:etvgh-blog-news&Itemid=484|publisher=e.tv Ghana|accessdate=8 July 2014|date=23 April 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714162720/http://www.etvghana.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=3634:etv-ghana-holds-maiden-edition-of-ghanas-most-influential-awards&catid=96:etvgh-blog-news&Itemid=484|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Life and music career==\nRebecca Acheampong was born in [[Kumasi]], Ghana. She is the first girl and fifth born of nine children.<ref>{{cite web|title=I grew up with my Step-mum \u2013 Becca|url=http://www.ghanamusic.com/news/top-stories/i-grew-up-with-my-step-mum-becca/index.html|website=GhanaMusic.com|publisher=News One|accessdate=28 June 2014|date=25 September 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714143758/http://www.ghanamusic.com/news/top-stories/i-grew-up-with-my-step-mum-becca/index.html|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> Becca was quite active in church and school activities during her childhood. She attended Morning Star and [[Wesley Girls' High School]]. She took an interest in showcasing her vocal dexterity at talent shows held at the latter school. She graduated from [[Croydon College]] and became a [[child care]] and education worker.<ref name=\"Peacefmonline.com \"/> Becca relocated to Ghana and signed with Kiki Banson's EKB Records.<ref name=\"Peacefmonline.com \"/> She studied at the [[Ghana Institute of Management and Public Administration]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://buzzghana.com/rebecca-acheampong-becca-10-lesser-known-facts-about-the-ghanaian-songstress/|title=Rebecca Acheampong (Becca) Bio: 10 Lesser Known Facts About Her|date=2015-11-03|website=BuzzGhana - Famous People, Celebrity Bios, Updates and Trendy News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n\n===2007:''Sugar''===\nBecca started working on her debut studio album ''Sugar'' in 2007. The album comprises 12 songs and was recorded in English and [[Twi]]. It was preceded by the lead single \"You Lied to Me\". The song was released in 2007 and features vocals from [[Kwabena Kwabena]]. The music video for the song was shot and directed in Ghana. On 13 November 2007, Becca launched the album in Ghana. She featured [[Hugh Masekela]] on the song \"I Love You\".<ref name=\"Peacefmonline.com \"/> ''Sugar'' was launched in South Africa alongside Hugh Masekela's album ''Live at the Market Theatre''.<ref name=\"Modern Ghana 1\"/>\n\n===2011\u20132013:''Time 4 Me''===\nBecca's second studio album ''Time 4 Me'' was released on 16 May 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ghanaian Singer, Becca Set To Launch Latest Album on the 16th Of May|url=http://1musicnetworks.tv/ghanaian-singer-becca-set-to-launch-latest-album-on-the-16th-of-may/|publisher=Music Network|accessdate=6 July 2014|date=6 May 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714235852/http://1musicnetworks.tv/ghanaian-singer-becca-set-to-launch-latest-album-on-the-16th-of-may/|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> Becca describes the album as a musical journey inspired by her thoughts, emotions and beliefs.<ref name=\"Daily Graphic\">{{cite web|last1=Yeboah|first1=Isaac|title=Becca, Kwame Yeboah launch at +233|url=http://graphic.com.gh/entertainment/showbiz-news/4450-becca-kwame-yeboah-launch-at-233.html|work=[[Daily Graphic (Ghana)|Daily Graphic]]|accessdate=7 July 2014|date=21 July 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714185529/http://graphic.com.gh/entertainment/showbiz-news/4450-becca-kwame-yeboah-launch-at-233.html|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> The album comprises 20 songs and features guest appearances from [[2face Idibia]], [[M.I Abaga|MI]], [[King Ayisoba]], Trigmatic, Jay Storm and Akwaboah. The album produced the singles \"Forever\", \"Push\", \"Bad Man Bad Girl\", \"No Away\" and \"Follow the Leader\". Ten thousand copies of the album were given to fans who bought the Thursday edition of ''Graphic Showbiz'' newspaper.<ref>{{cite web|title=Phenomenal BECCA launches album in unique style|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/artikel.php?ID=274262|publisher=Ghana Web|accessdate=7 July 2014|date=17 May 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141013192042/http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/artikel.php?ID=274262|archive-date=13 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> ''Time 4 Me'' was certified 2x platinum in Ghana.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Nii Atakora Mensah |title=Becca reveals her \u2018Time 4 Me\u2019 album track list |url=https://www.ghanamusic.com/news/top-stories/becca-reveals-her-time-4-me-track-list/index.html |publisher=Ghana Music.com |accessdate=19 February 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121104181201/https://www.ghanamusic.com/news/top-stories/becca-reveals-her-time-4-me-track-list/index.html |archivedate=4 November 2012 |date=11 August 2012}}</ref> Becca went on a nationwide campus tour to promote the album.<ref>{{cite web|title=Becca's \u2018Time 4 Me\u2019 album out on May 16; RLG sponsors free CD distribution|url=http://totalshowbiz.com/33448/beccas-time-4-me-album-to-be-released-on-may-16-rlg-sponsors-free-cd-distribution/|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140709180452/http://totalshowbiz.com/33448/beccas-time-4-me-album-to-be-released-on-may-16-rlg-sponsors-free-cd-distribution/|url-status=dead|archive-date=9 July 2014|publisher=Total Showbiz|accessdate=7 July 2014|date=7 May 2013}}</ref> Becca's 2011 single \"Africa Woman\" appeared as a bonus on the album; the song is a melodic ode to the strength and character of African women. The music video for \"African Woman\" was shot and directed in Ghana by Samad Davis; it starts with a quote and transitions into landscape scenes of Becca.<ref>{{cite web|title=Video:Ghanaian Star Becca releases music video for her track \u2013 \"African Woman\"|url=http://www.amcng.tv/ghanaian-star-becca-releases-music-video-for-her-track-african-woman/|publisher=AMC|accessdate=7 July 2014|date=21 March 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714221612/http://www.amcng.tv/ghanaian-star-becca-releases-music-video-for-her-track-african-woman/|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Diamonds get their character from the African Woman\" \u2013 Ghanaian Star Becca releases music video for her track \u2013 \"African Woman|url=http://www.bellanaija.com/2011/03/02/diamonds-get-their-character-from-the-african-woman-ghanaian-star-becca-releases-music-video-for-her-track-african-woman/|publisher=Bellanaija|accessdate=7 July 2014|date=2 March 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714185935/http://www.bellanaija.com/2011/03/02/diamonds-get-their-character-from-the-african-woman-ghanaian-star-becca-releases-music-video-for-her-track-african-woman/|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, Becca released \"Forever\" and \"Push\" as the album's lead and second singles. \"Push\" features guest vocals by [[King Ayisoba]] and Trigmatic. The music video for \"Push\" was uploaded to YouTube on 17 May 2011 and features cameo appearances from [[John Dumelo]], [[Yvonne Okoro]] and [[Yvonne Nelson]].<ref>{{cite web|title=New Music Video: \"Push\" Becca Featuring King Ayisoba and Trigmatic|url=http://showbiz.peacefmonline.com/pages/music/201105/42629.php|publisher=Peace FM Online|accessdate=7 July 2014|date=19 May 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714175416/http://showbiz.peacefmonline.com/pages/music/201105/42629.php|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> The album's third single \"Bad Man Bad Girl\" was released in February 2012; it features vocals by [[2face Idibia]] and was recorded in the summer of 2011. The music video for \"Bad Man Bad Girl\" was shot in Accra and other parts of Ghana.<ref>{{cite web|title=Becca Set To Release With 2Face|url=http://www.allghanadata.com/?id=1400-198-5&t=Becca-Set-To-Release-With-2Face|work=Daily Guide|accessdate=7 July 2014|date=14 June 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714221348/http://www.allghanadata.com/?id=1400-198-5&t=Becca-Set-To-Release-With-2Face|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\nThe [[M.I Abaga|MI]]-assisted track \"No Away\" was released on 22 June 2012, as the album's fourth single.<ref>{{cite web|title=New Music: Becca Feat. M.I \u2013 No Away|url=http://www.bellanaija.com/2012/06/22/new-music-becca-feat-m-i-no-away/|publisher=Bellanaija|accessdate=7 July 2014|date=22 June 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140812080150/http://www.bellanaija.com/2012/06/22/new-music-becca-feat-m-i-no-away/|archive-date=12 August 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> It was recorded in Ghana and Nigeria and mixed in South Africa. The music video for \"No Away\" was shot in South Africa and uploaded to YouTube on 12 August 2012, at a total length of 4 minutes and 11 seconds.<ref>{{cite web|title=New Video: Becca Feat. M.I \u2013 No Away|url=http://www.bellanaija.com/2012/08/13/new-video-becca-feat-m-i-no-away/|publisher=Bellanaija|accessdate=7 July 2014|date=13 August 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140910114634/http://www.bellanaija.com/2012/08/13/new-video-becca-feat-m-i-no-away/|archive-date=10 September 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> Liquor brand Kasapreko Company Limited and EKB Records spent $50,000 on the video shoot. The production cost for the video made it one of the most expensive videos released by a Ghanaian artist at that time.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ghana: Becca Drops $50,000 Song|url=http://www.showbizafrica.net/news/ghana-becca-drops-50-000-song/|publisher=Showbiz Africa|accessdate=7 July 2014|date=19 June 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714191306/http://www.showbizafrica.net/news/ghana-becca-drops-50-000-song/|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> The video was unveiled during a ceremony at the XL Club in Accra.<ref>{{cite web|title=Becca: I\u2019m Not A Big Fool|url=http://vibeghana.com/2012/07/23/becca-im-not-a-big-fool/|publisher=Vibe Ghana|accessdate=7 July 2014|date=23 June 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714181943/http://vibeghana.com/2012/07/23/becca-im-not-a-big-fool/|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 June 2013, Becca released the album's fifth single \"Follow the Leader\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Ghanaian Music Star Becca Returns with New Single 'Follow The Leader'|url=http://www.bellanaija.com/2013/06/18/ghanaian-music-star-becca-returns-with-new-single-follow-the-leader/|publisher=Bellanaija|accessdate=7 July 2014|date=18 June 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714212124/http://www.bellanaija.com/2013/06/18/ghanaian-music-star-becca-returns-with-new-single-follow-the-leader/|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> On 25 June 2013, EKB Records released the music video for her song \"Time 4 Me\", which was shot in [[Yokohama]] and Tokyo.<ref>{{cite web|title=Posts Tagged \u2018Becca \u2018Time 4 Me\u2019 Music Video\u2019|url=http://www.ghanacelebrities.com/tag/becca-time-4-me-music-video/|publisher=Ghana Celebrities|accessdate=7 July 2014|date=26 July 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714195838/http://www.ghanacelebrities.com/tag/becca-time-4-me-music-video/|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===2014:\"Move\" single featuring Uhuru===\n[[File:Becca_at_the_Ovation_Red_Carol_charity_ball.jpg|thumb|180px|right|Becca performing at the Ovation Red Carol charity ball in December 2013]]\nOn 12 April 2014, Becca released her single \"Move\". It features vocals by South African group [[Uhuru (music group)|Uhuru]] and debuted on Bola Ray's Drive Time show on [[Joy FM (Ghana)|Joy FM]]. It was produced by Kaywa and written by Becca and Kiki Banson.<ref>{{cite web|title=Merging Energy and Culture, MOVE-Another Great Music Video from Becca with Appearances By Legendary African musicians-Yvonne Chaka Chaka & Hughes Hugh Masekela|url=http://www.ghanafame.com/merging-energy-and-culture-move-another-great-music-video-from-becca-with-appearances-by-legendary-african-musicians-yvonne-chaka-chaka-hughes-hugh-masekela/|publisher=Ghana Fame|accessdate=7 July 2014|date=14 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714213938/http://www.ghanafame.com/merging-energy-and-culture-move-another-great-music-video-from-becca-with-appearances-by-legendary-african-musicians-yvonne-chaka-chaka-hughes-hugh-masekela/|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> The music video for \"Move\" was uploaded to YouTube on 1 May 2014; it features cameo appearances from [[Yvonne Chaka Chaka]] and [[Hugh Masekela]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Watch Ghanaian Singer Becca's New Video, \u2018Move,\u2019 featuring Uhuru|url=http://afripopmag.com/2014/05/watch-ghanaian-singer-beccas-new-video-move-featuring-uhuru/|publisher=afriPoP|accessdate=7 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714180230/http://afripopmag.com/2014/05/watch-ghanaian-singer-beccas-new-video-move-featuring-uhuru/|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> Kwame Dadzie of Flex Ghana reviewed the song and concluded its rhythm is a replica of \"[[Khona]]\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Becca's Latest Single 'Move'- A Replication of 'Khona'?|url=http://www.flexghana.com/index.php/street-gossip/item/1791-beccas-latest-single-move-a-replication-of-khona|publisher=Flex Ghana|accessdate=7 July 2014|date=21 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714170037/http://www.flexghana.com/index.php/street-gossip/item/1791-beccas-latest-single-move-a-replication-of-khona|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Artistry, humanitarian work and endorsements===\nBecca's upbringing and surroundings influenced her musical and fashion style. She has established a rescue organization which raises funds to help children affected by [[HIV/AIDS]] in Ghana.<ref name=\"Peacefmonline.com \"/> In 2014, she became a Goodwill ambassador for [[UNAIDS]].<ref name=\"Graphic Showbiz\">{{cite web|title=I won't be drawn back \u2013 Becca says after 'snub' at Ghana-Zambia match|url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/entertainment/2013/november-14th/i-wont-be-drawn-back-becca-says-after-snub-at-ghana-zambia-match.php|website=Joy Online|publisher=Graphic Showbiz|accessdate=6 July 2014|date=14 November 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714182414/http://www.myjoyonline.com/entertainment/2013/november-14th/i-wont-be-drawn-back-becca-says-after-snub-at-ghana-zambia-match.php|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> On 1 September 2009, [[Globacom|GLO]] Mobile Ghana unveiled Becca as one of its brand ambassadors.<ref>{{cite web|title=Glos make Becca ambassador|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2009/12/glos-make-becca-ambassador/|publisher=[[Vanguard (Nigeria)|Vanguard]]|accessdate=28 June 2014|date=18 December 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141017060436/http://www.vanguardngr.com/2009/12/glos-make-becca-ambassador/|archive-date=17 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> Moreover, the Ministry of Youth and Sports unveiled her as one of Ghana's official ambassadors for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=STARS UNVEILED AS WORLD CUP AMBASSADORS FOR GHANA|url=http://theheraldghana.com/stars-unveiled-world-cup-ambassadors-ghana/|accessdate=6 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305235432/http://theheraldghana.com/stars-unveiled-world-cup-ambassadors-ghana/|archive-date=5 March 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Notable performances===\nBecca performed at the [[Accra International Conference Centre]] for MTN's Heroes of Change television series finale.<ref>{{cite web|title=Becca, others for \u2018Heroes\u2019 finale|url=http://www.ghanaiannews.ca/becca-others-for-heroes-finale/|publisher=The Ghanaian News|accessdate=28 June 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714171307/http://www.ghanaiannews.ca/becca-others-for-heroes-finale/|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 26 July 2013, she performed with recording engineer Kwame Yeboah (and his Ohia beye Ya band) to launch her second studio album in Accra.<ref name=\"Daily Graphic\"/> On 20 December 2013, she headlined the third edition of the Girl Talk concert, which occurred at the [[National Theatre of Ghana]].<ref name=\"The Chronicle\"/> On 24 March 2014, Allsports Ghana reported that Becca would perform before the kickoff of [[Ghana Premier League]] matches to promote the league.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Yeboah|first1=Thomas|title=Becca to perform at Ghana premier league matches?|url=http://allsports.com.gh/columnist/becca-to-perform-at-ghana-premier-league-matches-id2749257.html|website=allsports.com|publisher=all Sports Ghana|accessdate=4 July 2014|date=24 March 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714162117/http://allsports.com.gh/columnist/becca-to-perform-at-ghana-premier-league-matches-id2749257.html|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Gender discrimination==\nBecca was scheduled to sing [[God Bless Our Homeland Ghana|Ghana's national anthem]] at the [[Baba Yara Stadium]] during the country's World Cup qualifier match against Zambia in September 2013. Unfortunately for her, she did not perform due to a directive by authorities in charge of the match. Becca expressed her dissatisfaction at the incident while speaking at the UN Cultural Night, which took place at the [[Alliance Fran\u00e7aise]] in Accra. A spokesperson for the Ghana Football Association told ''Graphic Showbiz'' they didn't know arrangements had been made for Becca to sing.<ref name=\"Graphic Showbiz\"/>\n\n==Personal life==\nBecca is married to Nigerian entrepreneur and artist manager Oluwatobi Sanni Daniel; the couple's wedding was held on 18 August 2018 in Accra.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://airnewsonline.com/photos-videos-beccas-traditional-wedding-tobi-sanni-daniel/|title=First beautiful photos & videos from Becca's traditional wedding with Tobi Sanni Daniel {{!}} AirnewsOnline|date=18 August 2018|work=AirnewsOnline|access-date=19 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180820005658/https://airnewsonline.com/photos-videos-beccas-traditional-wedding-tobi-sanni-daniel/|archive-date=20 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> She has one child; a baby girl.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.peacefmonline.com/pages/showbiz/news/201902/374571.php|title=What Is The Colour of Becca's Baby? \u2013 Blakofe Asks|last=Online|first=Peace FM|website=peacefmonline.com|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref> \n\n===Relationship controversy===\nBecca was at the center of her former manager (Kiki Banson)'s controversial divorce from his wife. Banson allegedly divorced his wife to marry Becca.<ref>{{cite web|title=Singer Becca Causes Manager \u2018Kiki Banson\u2019 To Divorce Wife For Her|url=http://omgghana.com/singer-becca-causes-manager-kiki-banson-to-divorce-wife-for-her/|publisher=OMG Ghana|accessdate=6 July 2014|date=30 April 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714201936/http://omgghana.com/singer-becca-causes-manager-kiki-banson-to-divorce-wife-for-her/|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Ghanaian singer Becca in a Husband Snatching Drama|url=http://www.thenigerianvoice.com/nvmovie/137126/3/ghanaian-singer-becca-in-a-husband-snatching-drama.html|publisher=The Nigerian Voice|accessdate=6 July 2014|date=5 February 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402154720/http://www.thenigerianvoice.com/nvmovie/137126/3/ghanaian-singer-becca-in-a-husband-snatching-drama.html|archive-date=2 April 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> The story went haywire after Becca's father reportedly disowned his daughter over her intentions to marry her manager.<ref>{{cite web|last1=James|first1=Osaremen|title=Sexy Ghanaian Singer, Becca Disowned By Dad Over Plans To Marry Married Manager|url=http://www.nigeriafilms.com/news/19502/37/sexy-ghanaian-singer-becca-disowned-by-dad-over-pl.html|publisher=Nigeria Films|accessdate=6 July 2014|date=11 November 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140727144723/http://www.nigeriafilms.com/news/19502/37/sexy-ghanaian-singer-becca-disowned-by-dad-over-pl.html|archive-date=27 July 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The \u2018Becca\u2019 story: Our gods must be crazy!|url=http://www.ghanaherald.com/the-becca-story-our-gods-must-be-crazy/|work=The Ghana Herald|accessdate=6 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714202922/http://www.ghanaherald.com/the-becca-story-our-gods-must-be-crazy/|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio albums===\n*''Sugar'' (2007)\n*''Time 4 Me'' (2013)\n*''Unveiling'' (2017)\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Event\n!Prize\n!Recipient\n!Result\n!Ref\n|-\n|2017\n|2017 Ghana Music Awards UK\n|Highlife Artiste of the Year\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Herself\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pulse.com.gh/entertainment/music/2017-ghana-music-awards-uk-stonebwoy-kumi-guitar-becca-others-bag-multiple-nominations-id6977020.html|title=2017 Ghana Music Awards UK Stonebwoy, Kumi Guitar, Becca, others bag multiple nominations|date=7 July 2017|website=|publisher=Pulse|accessdate=5 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171005154743/http://www.pulse.com.gh/entertainment/music/2017-ghana-music-awards-uk-stonebwoy-kumi-guitar-becca-others-bag-multiple-nominations-id6977020.html|archive-date=5 October 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|2014\n|[[City People Entertainment Awards]]\n|Musician of the Year (Female)\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=City People Announces 2014 Entertainment Awards Nominees|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/entertainment/artikel.php?