{"title_page": "Ravi Teja", "text_new": "{{for|the Indian cricketer|Ravi Teja (cricketer)}}\n{{Hatnote|This is a [[Telugu language|Telugu name]]; the family name is ''Bhupatiraju''.}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Ravi Teja\n| image         = [[File:RaviTejaLatest.jpg|frameless]]\n| caption       = \n| birth_name         = Ravi Shankar Raju Bhupatiraju\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1968|01|26}}\n| birth_place        = [[Jaggampeta]], [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[India]]\n| nationality        = Indian\n| occupation         = Actor\n| years_active       = 1990\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Kalyani|2000}}\n}}\n'''Ravi Teja''' (born as '''Ravi Shankar Raju Bhupatiraju''' on 26 January 1968)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150127/entertainment-tollywood/article/ravi-teja%E2%80%99s-intimate-party|title=Ravi Teja's intimate party|newspaper=[[Deccan Chronicle|DC]]|date=28 January 2015|accessdate=18 May 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160924130929/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150127/entertainment-tollywood/article/ravi-teja%E2%80%99s-intimate-party|archive-date=24 September 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Ravi Teja: Movies, Photos, Videos, News & Biography |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/topic/Ravi-Teja |author=<!-- Staff author(s); no byline --> |accessdate=30 June 2018 |work=The Times of India |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180723005859/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/topic/Ravi-Teja |archive-date=23 July 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> is an [[Indian film]] actor known for his work in [[Telugu cinema]]. Known for his roles in [[action comedy film]]s, he is widely considered one of the most popular and highest-paid actors of Telugu cinema, he is referred to as ''Mass Maharaj''. He won the [[Nandi Special Jury Award]] in 1999 and 2002 for his performance in the films ''[[Nee Kosam]]'' (1999) and ''[[Khadgam]]'' (2002) and also won the state [[Nandi Award]] for best actor for his film ''[[Neninthe]]'' in 2008.\n\nHe started his career as a supporting artist in ''[[Karthavyam (1990 film)|Karthavyam]]'' (1990) and subsequently played small roles in the films ''[[Chaitanya (film)|Chaitanya]]'' (1991), ''[[Aaj Ka Goonda Raj]]'' (1992), ''[[Allari Priyudu]]'' (1993), ''[[Ninne Pelladata]]'' (1996) and ''[[Sindhooram]]'' (1997). Teja has also worked as an assistant director for several Telugu films.\n\nRavi Teja began his professional career as a lead actor with ''[[Nee Kosam]]'' in 1999 and also received the Nandi Award for his performance. He then starred in films such as ''[[Itlu Sravani Subramanyam]]'' (2001), ''[[Chiranjeevulu (2001 film)|Chiranjeevulu]]'' (2001), ''[[Avunu Valliddaru Ista Paddaru!]]'' (2002), ''[[Idiot (2002 film)|Idiot]]'' (2002), ''[[Khadgam]]'' (2002), ''[[Amma Nanna O Tamila Ammayi]]'' (2003), ''[[Venky]]'' (2004), ''[[Naa Autograph]]'' (2004), ''[[Bhadra (2005 film)|Bhadra]]'' (2005), ''[[Vikramarkudu]]'' (2006), ''[[Dubai Seenu]]'' (2007), ''[[Krishna (2008 film)|Krishna]]'' (2008), ''[[Baladur]]'' (2008), ''[[Neninthe]]'' (2008), ''[[Kick (2009 film)|Kick]]'' (2009), ''[[Anjaneyulu (film)|Anjaneyulu]]'' (2009), ''[[Shambo Shiva Shambo]]'' (2010), ''[[Don Seenu]]'' (2010), ''[[Mirapakay]]'' (2011), ''[[Balupu]]'' (2013), ''[[Power (2014 Telugu film)|Power]]'' (2014), ''[[Bengal Tiger (2015 film)|Bengal Tiger]]'' (2015),  ''[[Raja the Great]]''  (2017) and \n''[[Amar Akbar Anthony (2018 film)|Amar Akbar Anthony]]''  (2018).\nIn 2012, he was also listed as 50th in the ''[[Forbes]]'' India list of top 100 Celebrities with an annual income of {{INRConvert|15.5|c}}.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://forbesindia.com/profile/ravi-teja/102|title=ayushForbes|magazine=[[Forbes India]]|date=13 January 2013|accessdate=11 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151017192010/http://forbesindia.com/profile/ravi-teja/102|archive-date=17 October 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2013 he was in 68th position with earnings of {{INRConvert|13|c}}.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://forbesindia.com/celebprofile/ravi-teja/136|title=Ravi Teja|magazine=[[Forbes India]]|date=13 October 2013|accessdate=11 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151019034032/http://forbesindia.com/celebprofile/ravi-teja/136|archive-date=19 October 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2015 he was in 74th position with earnings of {{INRConvert|12.5|c}}.\n\n==Early life==\nHe was born to Raj Gopal Raju and Rajya Lakshmi Bhupatiraju in  [[Kakinada]], Andhra Pradesh, India.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ravi Teja Profile |url=http://www.andhrareporter.com/stars/actors/tag/parents/bhupatiraju-rajgopal-raju/ |publisher=Andhra Reporter |accessdate=29 August 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121120001739/http://www.andhrareporter.com/stars/actors/tag/parents/bhupatiraju-rajgopal-raju |archivedate=20 November 2012 }}</ref> Teja 's father was a pharmacist and his mother was a homemaker. He is the eldest of three sons, the others being Bharath (died at 24 June 2017 in a car accident) and Raghu, who are also actors.<ref name=\"bio\">{{cite web|title=Ravi Teja Biography|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/celebs/ravi-teja/biography.html|publisher=One India|accessdate=29 August 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121201012402/http://entertainment.oneindia.in/celebs/ravi-teja/biography.html|archive-date=1 December 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> Teja spent most of his childhood in Northern India because his father used to move very often due to his work. His schooling was in [[Jaipur]], [[Delhi]], [[Mumbai]] and [[Bhopal]].<ref name=\"bio\" />  He is fluent in both Hindi and Telugu. Teja completed his schooling at N.S.M. Public School, Vijayawada. Later on he completed his Bachelors in Arts at Siddhartha Degree College, Vijayawada.  In 1988 he went to [[Chennai]] to start his career in films.<ref name=\"bio\" />\n\n==Career==\n{{Further|Ravi Teja filmography}}\n\n===1990\u20131996===\nIn his early years working in Chennai, [[YVS Chowdary]] and [[Gunasekhar]] were his roommates.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-05-29/news-interviews/29594494_1_ravi-teja-film-industry-chennai | work=The Times Of India | title=YVS, Gunasekhar & Ravi were rommates | date=29 May 2011 | access-date=10 April 2012 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130524133533/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-05-29/news-interviews/29594494_1_ravi-teja-film-industry-chennai | archive-date=24 May 2013 | url-status=live }}</ref> He had small roles in the films ''[[Karthavyam (1990 film)|Karthavyam]]'' (1990),  ''Chaitanya'' (1991) and ''[[Aaj Ka Goonda Raj]]'' (1992). Ravi became an assistant director, working in both television and film. As an assistant director, he worked in several Bollywood as well as Telugu projects including ''Prathihnbandh'', ''Aaj Ka Goonda Raj'', and ''[[Criminal (1994 film)|Criminal]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ravi Teja profile |url=http://www.totaltollywood.com/profiles/profiles.php?category=1&id=raviteja |publisher=total tollywood |accessdate=23 February 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111003122947/http://www.totaltollywood.com/profiles/profiles.php?category=1&id=raviteja |archive-date=3 October 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He met [[Krishna Vamsi]] and worked as an assistant director under him for the 1996 hit film ''[[Ninne Pelladutha]]''. Vamsi also gave Ravi the opportunity to act in a small role in that film. He continued to work as an assistant director for a few other films.<ref>{{cite web |title=ravi teja films |url=http://www.telugucolours.com/id1-pid16-chR/profile/ravi-teja |publisher=telugu colors |accessdate=23 February 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130524083358/http://www.telugucolours.com/id1-pid16-chR/profile/ravi-teja |archive-date=24 May 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===1997\u20132000===\nIn 1997, while still working as an assistant director, Ravi Teja got an opportunity to act in the film ''[[Sindhooram]]'' directed by Krishna Vamsi in a supporting role.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/did-you-know/Ravi-Teja-was-an-assistant-director/articleshow/15234882.cms|title=Ravi Teja was an assistant director - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref> The film won the [[National Film Award for Best Feature Film in Telugu]]. {{citation needed|date=April 2015}}\n\nRavi Teja followed up with roles in the films ''Seetha Rama Raju'', ''Padutha Teeyaga'', ''Manasichhi Choodu'' and [[S. V. Krishna Reddy|Krishna Reddy]]'s ''[[Premaku Velayara]]''. In 1999, he was cast in a leading role by [[Srinu Vaitla]] for ''[[Nee Kosam]]''. The film won the [[Nandi Award for Best Feature Film#Rajata (Silver) Nandi|Silver Nandi]] for Best Film. Ravi Teja won the [[Nandi Special Jury Award|Nandi Award for Best Actor Special Jury]] for his performance .{{citation needed|date=April 2015}}  Following this, he started appearing in more significant roles such as Krishna Vamsi's ''Samudram'', Chiranjeevi's ''[[Annayya (2000 film)|Annayya]]'' and ''[[Budget Padmanabham]]''. He also appeared in lead roles in multi-starrer films such as ''Kshemanga Velli Labanga Randi'', ''Tirumala Tirupathi Venkatesa'', ''Sakuntumba Sapari Vare Sametham'' and ''Ammayi Kosam''.\n\n===2001\u20132005===\nIn 2001, Teja's association with [[Puri Jagannadh]] began when he cast Ravi as the lead role in ''[[Itlu Sravani Subramanyam]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-iss.html |title=Telugu Cinema \u2013 Review \u2013 Itlu Sravani Subramanyam |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=14 September 2001 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121113061610/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-iss.html |archive-date=13 November 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> The movie was a commercial hit and got Ravi Teja credibility as a solo lead actor. In 2002, his next film ''[[Avunu Valliddaru Ista Paddaru!]]'', directed by [[Vamsy]] and co-starring [[Kaveri (actress)|Kalyani]] was released. The film was a successful at the box office and won Ravi acclaim.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-avunu.html |title=Telugu Cinema \u2013 Review \u2013 Avunu Valliddaru Ista Paddaru |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=2 August 2002 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121108132807/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-avunu.html |archive-date=8 November 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> The year also saw Ravi in ''[[Idiot (2002 film)|Idiot]]''. Directed by Puri Jagannadh and co-starring [[Rakshita]], it was a blockbuster hit and Ravi's performance and dialogue delivery were praised by critics and movie-goers alike.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://movies.fullhyderabad.com/idiot/telugu/idiot-movie-reviews-1689-2.html |title=Idiot review: Idiot (Telugu) Movie Review - fullhyd.com |publisher=Movies.fullhyderabad.com |date= |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130318054153/http://movies.fullhyderabad.com/idiot/telugu/idiot-movie-reviews-1689-2.html |archive-date=18 March 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-idiot.html |title=Telugu Cinema \u2013 Review \u2013 Idiot |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=22 August 2002 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121228002643/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-idiot.html |archive-date=28 December 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe year also saw the release of Krishna Vamsi's ''[[Khadgam]]''. The movie was a huge success at the box office and won the Sarojini Devi Award for a Film on National Integration. Ravi's portrayal of a young wannabe actor won him the [[Nandi Special Jury Award]] for the second time.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-khadgam.html |title=Telugu Cinema \u2013 Review \u2013 Khadgam |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date= |accessdate=17 September 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120815124116/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-khadgam.html |archive-date=15 August 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2003, Ravi again worked with director Puri Jagannadh for ''[[Amma Nanna O Tamila Ammayi]]''. The film co-starring [[Asin]] became a blockbuster hit and Jeevi of Idlebrain praised him: \"Ravi Teja did well. His strength lies in his dialogue delivery and reckless body language\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-anota.html |title=Telugu Cinema \u2013 Review \u2013 Amma Nanna O Tamil Ammai |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=19 April 2003 |accessdate=17 September 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120825115901/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-anota.html |archive-date=25 August 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> The year also saw Ravi working in commercially successful films such as ''[[Dongodu]]'', co-starring Kalyani and directed by Srinivas Bheemineni and ''[[Veede]]'', co-starring [[Aarthi Agarwal]] and directed by Ravi Raja Pinisetty. In the same year, Ravi was also seen in films such as ''Ee Abbayee Chala Manchodu'', ''Anveshana'' and ''Oka Raju Oka Rani'', which failed to do well at the box office.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-anveshana.html |title=Telugu Cinema \u2013 Review \u2013 Anveshana |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=27 December 2002 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140321071250/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-anveshana.html |archive-date=21 March 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-okarajuokarani.html |title=Telugu cinema review \u2013 Oka Raju Oka Rani |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=19 June 2003 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121226173131/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-okarajuokarani.html |archive-date=26 December 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-eacm.html |title=Telugu Cinema \u2013 Review \u2013 Ee Abbai Chala Manchodu |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=14 January 2003 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130730052122/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-eacm.html |archive-date=30 July 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn 2004, Ravi Teja co-starred in ''Venky'', directed by Srinu Vaitla. Idlebrain wrote: \"His comedy is very good in the first half. His antics with Siddanthi and the way he curses himself in front of the mirror is hilarious\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-venky.html |title=Telugu cinema Review \u2013 Venky |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=26 March 2004 |accessdate=17 September 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120926045108/http://idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-venky.html |archive-date=26 September 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> He appeared in ''[[Naa Autograph]]'' directed by cinematographer turned director [[S. Gopal Reddy]]. A critic from nowrunning.com wrote: \"Ravi Teja delivers a stunning performance as a dejected lover\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nowrunning.com/movie/1613/telugu/naa-autograph/278/review.htm |title=Naa Autograph Review \u2013 Telugu Movie Review by B. Anuradha |publisher=Nowrunning.com |date=12 August 2004 |accessdate=17 September 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120903024632/http://www.nowrunning.com/movie/1613/telugu/naa-autograph/278/review.htm |archive-date=3 September 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[Chanti (2004 film)|Chanti]]'' was directed by [[Sobhan]]. In 2005, Ravi Teja's work included ''[[Bhadra (2005 film)|Bhadra]]'', directed by [[Boyapati Srinu]] and ''[[Bhageeratha (film)|Bhageeratha]]'', directed by [[Rasool Ellore]]. He also worked in the crime film ''[[Shock (2006 film)|Shock]]'', directed by [[Harish Shankar]] and produced by Ram Gopal Varma.\n\n===2006\u20132011===\nIn 2006, Teja worked with director [[S. S. Rajamouli]] for ''[[Vikramarkudu]]''. This Film proved to be the highest-grossing film in Ravi Teja's career till then. Jeevi praised his performance: \"Vikramarkudu is the best film of Ravi Teja so far in histrionics aspect. He did both characters of Athali Sathi Babu and Vikram Rathod equally well, His mannerism of \"jintata\" is simply superb\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-vikramarkudu.html |title=Vikramarkudu \u2013 Telugu cinema Review |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=23 June 2006 |accessdate=17 September 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120918175435/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-vikramarkudu.html |archive-date=18 September 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Later in 2006, Ravi Teja acted in ''[[Khatarnak]]''. In 2007, Ravi Teja worked for the third time with director Srinu Vaitla for ''[[Dubai Seenu]]''. In 2008, Ravi Teja acted in ''[[Krishna (2008 film)|Krishna]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/35392.html |title='Krishna' it is, for Ravi Teja |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=19 December 2007 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141221011047/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/35392.html |archive-date=21 December 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> directed by [[V. V. Vinayak]].\nIn August 2008, Ravi Teja acted in ''[[Baladur]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/40744.html |title='Baladoor' for release on August 14 |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=13 August 2008 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141220232518/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/40744.html |archive-date=20 December 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> Later in that year, Ravi Teja again collaborated with director Puri Jagganath for ''[[Neninthe]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/34064.html |title=Puri to direct Raviteja for 'Neninthe' |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=12 October 2007 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141220235527/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/34064.html |archive-date=20 December 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> Although the film was not successful at the box office, Ravi Teja's portrayal of an up-and-coming assistant director in the film received acclaim.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-neninthe.html |title=Neninthe review \u2013 Telugu cinema Review |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=18 December 2008 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120414163719/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-neninthe.html |archive-date=14 April 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, Ravi Teja worked with director [[Surender Reddy]] for ''[[Kick (2009 film)|Kick]]''. Later that year, he appeared in ''[[Anjaneyulu (film)|Anjaneyulu]]''. In 2010, his films included ''[[Shambo Shiva Shambo]]'' and ''[[Don Seenu]]'', directed by [[Gopichand Malineni]].\n\nHis first release in 2011 was [[Harish Shankar]]'s ''[[Mirapakay]]''. He later starred in [[Ram Gopal Varma]]'s ''[[Dongala Mutha]]'' and made a cameo  appearance in ''[[Katha Screenplay Darshakatvam Appalaraju]]'', also directed by Ram Gopal Varma. His last release of the year was Ramesh Varma's ''[[Veera (2011 film)|Veera]]''. Later after this film, he went on to become \"Mass Maharaja' for his mass action scenes and nasty fights\n\n===2012\u2013present===\nHis first release in 2012 was [[Gunasekhar]]'s ''[[Nippu]]''. His next release was [[Siva (director)|Siva]]'s ''[[Daruvu]]''. \nHis next release was [[Puri Jagannadh]]'s ''[[Devudu Chesina Manushulu (2012 film)|Devudu Chesina Manushulu]]''. His last release in 2012 was [[Parasuram (director)|Parasuram]]'s ''[[Sarocharu]] '' Rediff.com wrote: \"Ravi Teja is in a different avatar, a more subdued one. A change of image and role is necessary for an actor and Ravi Teja makes the transition fairly well\".<ref>[http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-ravi-tejas-different-image-in-sarocharu/20121221.htm Review: Ravi Teja's different image in Sarocharu \u2013 Rediff.com Movies] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130131143159/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-ravi-tejas-different-image-in-sarocharu/20121221.htm |date=31 January 2013 }}. Rediff.com (21 December 2012). Retrieved on 26 July 2016.</ref>\n\n\nHis release in 2013 was Gopichand Malineni's action entertainer'' [[Balupu]]''. The Times of India wrote \"Ravi Teja has come up with an entertaining performance. His characterization and the flashback episode as Kancharapalem Shankar looked very powerful on the screen. He gets into the skin of the character and has done well.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-06-28/news-interviews/40254938_1_gopichand-malineni-ravi-teja-don-seenu|title=Balupu Telugu movie review highlights|newspaper=The Times of India|accessdate=28 June 2013<!-- 11:56 AM IST-->|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130701033203/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-06-28/news-interviews/40254938_1_gopichand-malineni-ravi-teja-don-seenu|archive-date=1 July 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> The film turned one of the biggest critical and commercial success of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/487954/20130709/balupu-box-office-collection-ravi-teja-sahasam.htm|title='Balupu' Box Office Collection: Ravi Teja Film Declared Smash Hit in US, Earns \u20b92 Crore|publisher=IBTimes|accessdate=9 July 2013<!-- 12:40 PM IST-->|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130714055025/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/487954/20130709/balupu-box-office-collection-ravi-teja-sahasam.htm|archive-date=14 July 2013|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/485456/20130702/balupu-box-office-collection-ravi-teja-kick.htm|title='Balupu' Box Office Collection: Ravi Teja Film Earns \u20b91.76 Crore Overseas, Beats 'Kick', 'Don Seenu' and 'Mirapakai'|publisher=IBTimes|accessdate=2 July 2013<!-- 11:41 AM IST-->|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130705204806/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/485456/20130702/balupu-box-office-collection-ravi-teja-kick.htm|archive-date=5 July 2013|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, he made a cameo appearance in Sairam Shankar's ''[[Romeo (2012 Telugu film)|Romeo]]'' and ''[[Power (2014 Telugu film)|Power]]'' with debutant director [[K. S. Ravindra]].\nIn 2015 he starred in ''[[Kick 2]]'', directed by [[Surender Reddy]] and produced by [[Nandamuri Kalyan Ram]].<ref>[http://www.indiaglitz.com/kick-2-release-date-confirmed-officially-telugu-news-128916 \"Kick2 release date\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150330231524/http://www.indiaglitz.com/kick-2-release-date-confirmed-officially-telugu-news-128916 |date=30 March 2015 }}. Indiaglitz.com (27 March 2015). Retrieved on 26 July 2016.</ref> Despite huge expectations, the film was a box office failure. After this he started a film titled ''[[Bengal Tiger (2015 film)|Bengal Tiger]]'', directed by [[Sampath Nandi]].<ref>[http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150130/entertainment-tollywood/article/new-start \"Ravi Teja's Bengal Tiger\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205095350/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150130/entertainment-tollywood/article/new-start |date=5 February 2015 }}. Deccanchronicle.com. Retrieved on 26 July 2016.</ref> This film grossed nearly {{INRConvert|40.5|c}}s globally and also became the 8th highest grossing Telugu film of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/baahubali-kumari-21f-top-20-highest-grossing-telugu-tollywood-movies-2015-662060|title=Baahubali to Kumari 21F: Top 20 highest-grossing Telugu/Tollywood movies of 2015|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|work=International Business Times India|date=5 January 2016|accessdate=5 January 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160105145832/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/baahubali-kumari-21f-top-20-highest-grossing-telugu-tollywood-movies-2015-662060|archivedate=5 January 2016}}</ref>\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://theplaybook.co/ravi-teja-upcoming-movies-list-2017-2018-tamil-telugu/|title=Ravi Teja Upcoming Movies|website=theplaybook.co|access-date=31 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170901022944/http://theplaybook.co/ravi-teja-upcoming-movies-list-2017-2018-tamil-telugu/|archive-date=1 September 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAfter taking a sabbatical for one year, he started two films ''[[Touch Chesi Chudu]]'' and ''[[Raja the Great]]'' (2017). While Raja The Great was a huge hit, becoming Ravi Teja's career's highest grosser, Touch Chesi Chudu was a big flop in both domestic and overseas. His next film was ''[[Amar Akbar Anthony (2018 film)|Amar Akbar Anthony]]'' directed by [[Sreenu Vaitla]].\n\n===Brand endorsement===\nRavi Teja was signed in as [[brand ambassador]] for Lunar \u2013 footwear and sandals in two states, [[Andhra Pradesh]] and [[Telangana]].<ref>[http://www.indiaglitz.com/finally-ravi-teja-signs-his-first-commercial-telugu-news-132647.html \"Finally Ravi Teja signs his first commercial IndiaGlitz Retrieved 15.05.2015\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150516000047/http://www.indiaglitz.com/finally-ravi-teja-signs-his-first-commercial-telugu-news-132647.html |date=16 May 2015 }}. Indiaglitz.com (13 May 2015). Retrieved on 26 July 2016.</ref> He later endorsed the liquor brand Lord & Master.<ref>[http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/star-hero-to-endorse-a-liquor-brand.html \"Star hero to endorse a liquor brand\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150611003235/http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/star-hero-to-endorse-a-liquor-brand.html |date=11 June 2015 }}. 123telugu.com. Retrieved on 26 July 2016.</ref><ref>[http://www.indiaglitz.com/ravi-teja-to-endorse-lord-and-master-brandy-telugu-news-134988.html \"Ravi Teja endorses Lord & Master\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150612080720/http://www.indiaglitz.com/ravi-teja-to-endorse-lord-and-master-brandy-telugu-news-134988.html |date=12 June 2015 }}. Indiaglitz.com (10 June 2015). Retrieved on 26 July 2016.</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{{Main|Ravi Teja filmography}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Indian film actors]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*{{Facebook|itsraviteja}}\n* {{IMDb name|id= 0712433|name=Ravi Teja }}\n* {{Rotten-tomatoes-person| ravi_teja|Ravi Teja }}\n\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n\n{{Nandi Award for Best Actor}}\n{{NandiSpecialJuryAward}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Teja, Ravi}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Telugu people]]\n[[Category:Telugu male actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Andhra Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Telugu cinema]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Hindi cinema]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Nandi Award winners]]\n[[Category:People from East Godavari district]]\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the Indian cricketer|Ravi Teja (cricketer)}}\n{{Hatnote|This is a [[Telugu language|Telugu name]]; the family name is ''Bhupatiraju''.}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Ravi Teja\n| image         = [[File:RaviTejaLatest.jpg|frameless]]\n| caption       = \n| birth_name         = Ravi Shankar Raju Bhupatiraju\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1968|01|26}}\n| birth_place        = [[Jaggampeta]], [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[India]]\n| nationality        = Indian\n| occupation         = Actor\n| years_active       = 1990\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Kalyani|2000}}\n}}\n'''Ravi Teja''' (born as '''Ravi Shankar Raju Bhupatiraju''' on 26 January 1968)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150127/entertainment-tollywood/article/ravi-teja%E2%80%99s-intimate-party|title=Ravi Teja's intimate party|newspaper=[[Deccan Chronicle|DC]]|date=28 January 2015|accessdate=18 May 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160924130929/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150127/entertainment-tollywood/article/ravi-teja%E2%80%99s-intimate-party|archive-date=24 September 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Ravi Teja: Movies, Photos, Videos, News & Biography |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/topic/Ravi-Teja |author=<!-- Staff author(s); no byline --> |accessdate=30 June 2018 |work=The Times of India |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180723005859/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/topic/Ravi-Teja |archive-date=23 July 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> is an [[Indian film]] actor known for his work in [[Telugu cinema]]. Known for his roles in [[action comedy film]]s, he is widely considered one of the most popular and highest-paid actors of Telugu cinema,{{cn|date=January 2020}} who has appeared in over [[Ravi Teja filmography|sixty films]]. He won the [[Nandi Special Jury Award]] in 1999 and 2002 for his performance in the films ''[[Nee Kosam]]'' (1999) and ''[[Khadgam]]'' (2002) and also won the state [[Nandi Award]] for best actor for his film ''[[Neninthe]]'' in 2008.\n\nHe started his career as a supporting artist in ''[[Karthavyam (1990 film)|Karthavyam]]'' (1990) and subsequently played small roles in the films ''[[Chaitanya (film)|Chaitanya]]'' (1991), ''[[Aaj Ka Goonda Raj]]'' (1992), ''[[Allari Priyudu]]'' (1993), ''[[Ninne Pelladata]]'' (1996) and ''[[Sindhooram]]'' (1997). Teja has also worked as an assistant director for several Telugu films.\n\nRavi Teja began his professional career as a lead actor with ''[[Nee Kosam]]'' in 1999 and also received the Nandi Award for his performance. He then starred in films such as ''[[Itlu Sravani Subramanyam]]'' (2001), ''[[Chiranjeevulu (2001 film)|Chiranjeevulu]]'' (2001), ''[[Avunu Valliddaru Ista Paddaru!]]'' (2002), ''[[Idiot (2002 film)|Idiot]]'' (2002), ''[[Khadgam]]'' (2002), ''[[Amma Nanna O Tamila Ammayi]]'' (2003), ''[[Venky]]'' (2004), ''[[Naa Autograph]]'' (2004), ''[[Bhadra (2005 film)|Bhadra]]'' (2005), ''[[Vikramarkudu]]'' (2006), ''[[Dubai Seenu]]'' (2007), ''[[Krishna (2008 film)|Krishna]]'' (2008), ''[[Baladur]]'' (2008), ''[[Neninthe]]'' (2008), ''[[Kick (2009 film)|Kick]]'' (2009), ''[[Anjaneyulu (film)|Anjaneyulu]]'' (2009), ''[[Shambo Shiva Shambo]]'' (2010), ''[[Don Seenu]]'' (2010), ''[[Mirapakay]]'' (2011), ''[[Balupu]]'' (2013), ''[[Power (2014 Telugu film)|Power]]'' (2014), ''[[Bengal Tiger (2015 film)|Bengal Tiger]]'' (2015),  ''[[Raja the Great]]''  (2017) and \n''[[Amar Akbar Anthony (2018 film)|Amar Akbar Anthony]]''  (2018).\nIn 2012, he was also listed as 50th in the ''[[Forbes]]'' India list of top 100 Celebrities with an annual income of {{INRConvert|15.5|c}}.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://forbesindia.com/profile/ravi-teja/102|title=ayushForbes|magazine=[[Forbes India]]|date=13 January 2013|accessdate=11 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151017192010/http://forbesindia.com/profile/ravi-teja/102|archive-date=17 October 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2013 he was in 68th position with earnings of {{INRConvert|13|c}}.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://forbesindia.com/celebprofile/ravi-teja/136|title=Ravi Teja|magazine=[[Forbes India]]|date=13 October 2013|accessdate=11 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151019034032/http://forbesindia.com/celebprofile/ravi-teja/136|archive-date=19 October 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2015 he was in 74th position with earnings of {{INRConvert|12.5|c}}.\n\n==Early life==\nHe was born to Raj Gopal Raju and Rajya Lakshmi Bhupatiraju in  [[Kakinada]], Andhra Pradesh, India.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ravi Teja Profile |url=http://www.andhrareporter.com/stars/actors/tag/parents/bhupatiraju-rajgopal-raju/ |publisher=Andhra Reporter |accessdate=29 August 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121120001739/http://www.andhrareporter.com/stars/actors/tag/parents/bhupatiraju-rajgopal-raju |archivedate=20 November 2012 }}</ref> Teja 's father was a pharmacist and his mother was a homemaker. He is the eldest of three sons, the others being Bharath (died at 24 June 2017 in a car accident) and Raghu, who are also actors.<ref name=\"bio\">{{cite web|title=Ravi Teja Biography|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/celebs/ravi-teja/biography.html|publisher=One India|accessdate=29 August 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121201012402/http://entertainment.oneindia.in/celebs/ravi-teja/biography.html|archive-date=1 December 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> Teja spent most of his childhood in Northern India because his father used to move very often due to his work. His schooling was in [[Jaipur]], [[Delhi]], [[Mumbai]] and [[Bhopal]].<ref name=\"bio\" />  He is fluent in both Hindi and Telugu. Teja completed his schooling at N.S.M. Public School, Vijayawada. Later on he completed his Bachelors in Arts at Siddhartha Degree College, Vijayawada.  In 1988 he went to [[Chennai]] to start his career in films.<ref name=\"bio\" />\n\n==Career==\n{{Further|Ravi Teja filmography}}\n\n===1990\u20131996===\nIn his early years working in Chennai, [[YVS Chowdary]] and [[Gunasekhar]] were his roommates.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-05-29/news-interviews/29594494_1_ravi-teja-film-industry-chennai | work=The Times Of India | title=YVS, Gunasekhar & Ravi were rommates | date=29 May 2011 | access-date=10 April 2012 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130524133533/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-05-29/news-interviews/29594494_1_ravi-teja-film-industry-chennai | archive-date=24 May 2013 | url-status=live }}</ref> He had small roles in the films ''[[Karthavyam (1990 film)|Karthavyam]]'' (1990),  ''Chaitanya'' (1991) and ''[[Aaj Ka Goonda Raj]]'' (1992). Ravi became an assistant director, working in both television and film. As an assistant director, he worked in several Bollywood as well as Telugu projects including ''Prathihnbandh'', ''Aaj Ka Goonda Raj'', and ''[[Criminal (1994 film)|Criminal]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ravi Teja profile |url=http://www.totaltollywood.com/profiles/profiles.php?category=1&id=raviteja |publisher=total tollywood |accessdate=23 February 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111003122947/http://www.totaltollywood.com/profiles/profiles.php?category=1&id=raviteja |archive-date=3 October 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He met [[Krishna Vamsi]] and worked as an assistant director under him for the 1996 hit film ''[[Ninne Pelladutha]]''. Vamsi also gave Ravi the opportunity to act in a small role in that film. He continued to work as an assistant director for a few other films.<ref>{{cite web |title=ravi teja films |url=http://www.telugucolours.com/id1-pid16-chR/profile/ravi-teja |publisher=telugu colors |accessdate=23 February 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130524083358/http://www.telugucolours.com/id1-pid16-chR/profile/ravi-teja |archive-date=24 May 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===1997\u20132000===\nIn 1997, while still working as an assistant director, Ravi Teja got an opportunity to act in the film ''[[Sindhooram]]'' directed by Krishna Vamsi in a supporting role.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/did-you-know/Ravi-Teja-was-an-assistant-director/articleshow/15234882.cms|title=Ravi Teja was an assistant director - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref> The film won the [[National Film Award for Best Feature Film in Telugu]]. {{citation needed|date=April 2015}}\n\nRavi Teja followed up with roles in the films ''Seetha Rama Raju'', ''Padutha Teeyaga'', ''Manasichhi Choodu'' and [[S. V. Krishna Reddy|Krishna Reddy]]'s ''[[Premaku Velayara]]''. In 1999, he was cast in a leading role by [[Srinu Vaitla]] for ''[[Nee Kosam]]''. The film won the [[Nandi Award for Best Feature Film#Rajata (Silver) Nandi|Silver Nandi]] for Best Film. Ravi Teja won the [[Nandi Special Jury Award|Nandi Award for Best Actor Special Jury]] for his performance .{{citation needed|date=April 2015}}  Following this, he started appearing in more significant roles such as Krishna Vamsi's ''Samudram'', Chiranjeevi's ''[[Annayya (2000 film)|Annayya]]'' and ''[[Budget Padmanabham]]''. He also appeared in lead roles in multi-starrer films such as ''Kshemanga Velli Labanga Randi'', ''Tirumala Tirupathi Venkatesa'', ''Sakuntumba Sapari Vare Sametham'' and ''Ammayi Kosam''.\n\n===2001\u20132005===\nIn 2001, Teja's association with [[Puri Jagannadh]] began when he cast Ravi as the lead role in ''[[Itlu Sravani Subramanyam]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-iss.html |title=Telugu Cinema \u2013 Review \u2013 Itlu Sravani Subramanyam |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=14 September 2001 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121113061610/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-iss.html |archive-date=13 November 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> The movie was a commercial hit and got Ravi Teja credibility as a solo lead actor. In 2002, his next film ''[[Avunu Valliddaru Ista Paddaru!]]'', directed by [[Vamsy]] and co-starring [[Kaveri (actress)|Kalyani]] was released. The film was a successful at the box office and won Ravi acclaim.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-avunu.html |title=Telugu Cinema \u2013 Review \u2013 Avunu Valliddaru Ista Paddaru |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=2 August 2002 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121108132807/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-avunu.html |archive-date=8 November 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> The year also saw Ravi in ''[[Idiot (2002 film)|Idiot]]''. Directed by Puri Jagannadh and co-starring [[Rakshita]], it was a blockbuster hit and Ravi's performance and dialogue delivery were praised by critics and movie-goers alike.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://movies.fullhyderabad.com/idiot/telugu/idiot-movie-reviews-1689-2.html |title=Idiot review: Idiot (Telugu) Movie Review - fullhyd.com |publisher=Movies.fullhyderabad.com |date= |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130318054153/http://movies.fullhyderabad.com/idiot/telugu/idiot-movie-reviews-1689-2.html |archive-date=18 March 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-idiot.html |title=Telugu Cinema \u2013 Review \u2013 Idiot |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=22 August 2002 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121228002643/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-idiot.html |archive-date=28 December 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe year also saw the release of Krishna Vamsi's ''[[Khadgam]]''. The movie was a huge success at the box office and won the Sarojini Devi Award for a Film on National Integration. Ravi's portrayal of a young wannabe actor won him the [[Nandi Special Jury Award]] for the second time.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-khadgam.html |title=Telugu Cinema \u2013 Review \u2013 Khadgam |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date= |accessdate=17 September 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120815124116/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-khadgam.html |archive-date=15 August 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2003, Ravi again worked with director Puri Jagannadh for ''[[Amma Nanna O Tamila Ammayi]]''. The film co-starring [[Asin]] became a blockbuster hit and Jeevi of Idlebrain praised him: \"Ravi Teja did well. His strength lies in his dialogue delivery and reckless body language\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-anota.html |title=Telugu Cinema \u2013 Review \u2013 Amma Nanna O Tamil Ammai |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=19 April 2003 |accessdate=17 September 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120825115901/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-anota.html |archive-date=25 August 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> The year also saw Ravi working in commercially successful films such as ''[[Dongodu]]'', co-starring Kalyani and directed by Srinivas Bheemineni and ''[[Veede]]'', co-starring [[Aarthi Agarwal]] and directed by Ravi Raja Pinisetty. In the same year, Ravi was also seen in films such as ''Ee Abbayee Chala Manchodu'', ''Anveshana'' and ''Oka Raju Oka Rani'', which failed to do well at the box office.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-anveshana.html |title=Telugu Cinema \u2013 Review \u2013 Anveshana |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=27 December 2002 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140321071250/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-anveshana.html |archive-date=21 March 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-okarajuokarani.html |title=Telugu cinema review \u2013 Oka Raju Oka Rani |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=19 June 2003 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121226173131/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-okarajuokarani.html |archive-date=26 December 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-eacm.html |title=Telugu Cinema \u2013 Review \u2013 Ee Abbai Chala Manchodu |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=14 January 2003 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130730052122/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-eacm.html |archive-date=30 July 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn 2004, Ravi Teja co-starred in ''Venky'', directed by Srinu Vaitla. Idlebrain wrote: \"His comedy is very good in the first half. His antics with Siddanthi and the way he curses himself in front of the mirror is hilarious\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-venky.html |title=Telugu cinema Review \u2013 Venky |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=26 March 2004 |accessdate=17 September 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120926045108/http://idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-venky.html |archive-date=26 September 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> He appeared in ''[[Naa Autograph]]'' directed by cinematographer turned director [[S. Gopal Reddy]]. A critic from nowrunning.com wrote: \"Ravi Teja delivers a stunning performance as a dejected lover\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nowrunning.com/movie/1613/telugu/naa-autograph/278/review.htm |title=Naa Autograph Review \u2013 Telugu Movie Review by B. Anuradha |publisher=Nowrunning.com |date=12 August 2004 |accessdate=17 September 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120903024632/http://www.nowrunning.com/movie/1613/telugu/naa-autograph/278/review.htm |archive-date=3 September 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[Chanti (2004 film)|Chanti]]'' was directed by [[Sobhan]]. In 2005, Ravi Teja's work included ''[[Bhadra (2005 film)|Bhadra]]'', directed by [[Boyapati Srinu]] and ''[[Bhageeratha (film)|Bhageeratha]]'', directed by [[Rasool Ellore]]. He also worked in the crime film ''[[Shock (2006 film)|Shock]]'', directed by [[Harish Shankar]] and produced by Ram Gopal Varma.\n\n===2006\u20132011===\nIn 2006, Teja worked with director [[S. S. Rajamouli]] for ''[[Vikramarkudu]]''. This Film proved to be the highest-grossing film in Ravi Teja's career till then. Jeevi praised his performance: \"Vikramarkudu is the best film of Ravi Teja so far in histrionics aspect. He did both characters of Athali Sathi Babu and Vikram Rathod equally well, His mannerism of \"jintata\" is simply superb\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-vikramarkudu.html |title=Vikramarkudu \u2013 Telugu cinema Review |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=23 June 2006 |accessdate=17 September 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120918175435/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-vikramarkudu.html |archive-date=18 September 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Later in 2006, Ravi Teja acted in ''[[Khatarnak]]''. In 2007, Ravi Teja worked for the third time with director Srinu Vaitla for ''[[Dubai Seenu]]''. In 2008, Ravi Teja acted in ''[[Krishna (2008 film)|Krishna]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/35392.html |title='Krishna' it is, for Ravi Teja |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=19 December 2007 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141221011047/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/35392.html |archive-date=21 December 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> directed by [[V. V. Vinayak]].\nIn August 2008, Ravi Teja acted in ''[[Baladur]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/40744.html |title='Baladoor' for release on August 14 |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=13 August 2008 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141220232518/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/40744.html |archive-date=20 December 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> Later in that year, Ravi Teja again collaborated with director Puri Jagganath for ''[[Neninthe]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/34064.html |title=Puri to direct Raviteja for 'Neninthe' |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=12 October 2007 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141220235527/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/34064.html |archive-date=20 December 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> Although the film was not successful at the box office, Ravi Teja's portrayal of an up-and-coming assistant director in the film received acclaim.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-neninthe.html |title=Neninthe review \u2013 Telugu cinema Review |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=18 December 2008 |accessdate=26 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120414163719/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-neninthe.html |archive-date=14 April 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, Ravi Teja worked with director [[Surender Reddy]] for ''[[Kick (2009 film)|Kick]]''. Later that year, he appeared in ''[[Anjaneyulu (film)|Anjaneyulu]]''. In 2010, his films included ''[[Shambo Shiva Shambo]]'' and ''[[Don Seenu]]'', directed by [[Gopichand Malineni]].\n\nHis first release in 2011 was [[Harish Shankar]]'s ''[[Mirapakay]]''. He later starred in [[Ram Gopal Varma]]'s ''[[Dongala Mutha]]'' and made a cameo  appearance in ''[[Katha Screenplay Darshakatvam Appalaraju]]'', also directed by Ram Gopal Varma. His last release of the year was Ramesh Varma's ''[[Veera (2011 film)|Veera]]''. Later after this film, he went on to become \"Mass Maharaja' for his mass action scenes and nasty fights\n\n===2012\u2013present===\nHis first release in 2012 was [[Gunasekhar]]'s ''[[Nippu]]''. His next release was [[Siva (director)|Siva]]'s ''[[Daruvu]]''. \nHis next release was [[Puri Jagannadh]]'s ''[[Devudu Chesina Manushulu (2012 film)|Devudu Chesina Manushulu]]''. His last release in 2012 was [[Parasuram (director)|Parasuram]]'s ''[[Sarocharu]] '' Rediff.com wrote: \"Ravi Teja is in a different avatar, a more subdued one. A change of image and role is necessary for an actor and Ravi Teja makes the transition fairly well\".<ref>[http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-ravi-tejas-different-image-in-sarocharu/20121221.htm Review: Ravi Teja's different image in Sarocharu \u2013 Rediff.com Movies] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130131143159/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-ravi-tejas-different-image-in-sarocharu/20121221.htm |date=31 January 2013 }}. Rediff.com (21 December 2012). Retrieved on 26 July 2016.</ref>\n\n\nHis release in 2013 was Gopichand Malineni's action entertainer'' [[Balupu]]''. The Times of India wrote \"Ravi Teja has come up with an entertaining performance. His characterization and the flashback episode as Kancharapalem Shankar looked very powerful on the screen. He gets into the skin of the character and has done well.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-06-28/news-interviews/40254938_1_gopichand-malineni-ravi-teja-don-seenu|title=Balupu Telugu movie review highlights|newspaper=The Times of India|accessdate=28 June 2013<!-- 11:56 AM IST-->|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130701033203/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-06-28/news-interviews/40254938_1_gopichand-malineni-ravi-teja-don-seenu|archive-date=1 July 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> The film turned one of the biggest critical and commercial success of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/487954/20130709/balupu-box-office-collection-ravi-teja-sahasam.htm|title='Balupu' Box Office Collection: Ravi Teja Film Declared Smash Hit in US, Earns \u20b92 Crore|publisher=IBTimes|accessdate=9 July 2013<!-- 12:40 PM IST-->|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130714055025/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/487954/20130709/balupu-box-office-collection-ravi-teja-sahasam.htm|archive-date=14 July 2013|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/485456/20130702/balupu-box-office-collection-ravi-teja-kick.htm|title='Balupu' Box Office Collection: Ravi Teja Film Earns \u20b91.76 Crore Overseas, Beats 'Kick', 'Don Seenu' and 'Mirapakai'|publisher=IBTimes|accessdate=2 July 2013<!-- 11:41 AM IST-->|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130705204806/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/485456/20130702/balupu-box-office-collection-ravi-teja-kick.htm|archive-date=5 July 2013|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, he made a cameo appearance in Sairam Shankar's ''[[Romeo (2012 Telugu film)|Romeo]]'' and ''[[Power (2014 Telugu film)|Power]]'' with debutant director [[K. S. Ravindra]].\nIn 2015 he starred in ''[[Kick 2]]'', directed by [[Surender Reddy]] and produced by [[Nandamuri Kalyan Ram]].<ref>[http://www.indiaglitz.com/kick-2-release-date-confirmed-officially-telugu-news-128916 \"Kick2 release date\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150330231524/http://www.indiaglitz.com/kick-2-release-date-confirmed-officially-telugu-news-128916 |date=30 March 2015 }}. Indiaglitz.com (27 March 2015). Retrieved on 26 July 2016.</ref> Despite huge expectations, the film was a box office failure. After this he started a film titled ''[[Bengal Tiger (2015 film)|Bengal Tiger]]'', directed by [[Sampath Nandi]].<ref>[http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150130/entertainment-tollywood/article/new-start \"Ravi Teja's Bengal Tiger\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205095350/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150130/entertainment-tollywood/article/new-start |date=5 February 2015 }}. Deccanchronicle.com. Retrieved on 26 July 2016.</ref> This film grossed nearly {{INRConvert|40.5|c}}s globally and also became the 8th highest grossing Telugu film of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/baahubali-kumari-21f-top-20-highest-grossing-telugu-tollywood-movies-2015-662060|title=Baahubali to Kumari 21F: Top 20 highest-grossing Telugu/Tollywood movies of 2015|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|work=International Business Times India|date=5 January 2016|accessdate=5 January 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160105145832/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/baahubali-kumari-21f-top-20-highest-grossing-telugu-tollywood-movies-2015-662060|archivedate=5 January 2016}}</ref>\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://theplaybook.co/ravi-teja-upcoming-movies-list-2017-2018-tamil-telugu/|title=Ravi Teja Upcoming Movies|website=theplaybook.co|access-date=31 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170901022944/http://theplaybook.co/ravi-teja-upcoming-movies-list-2017-2018-tamil-telugu/|archive-date=1 September 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAfter taking a sabbatical for one year, he started two films ''[[Touch Chesi Chudu]]'' and ''[[Raja the Great]]'' (2017). While Raja The Great was a huge hit, becoming Ravi Teja's career's highest grosser, Touch Chesi Chudu was a big flop in both domestic and overseas. His next film was ''[[Amar Akbar Anthony (2018 film)|Amar Akbar Anthony]]'' directed by [[Sreenu Vaitla]].\n\n===Brand endorsement===\nRavi Teja was signed in as [[brand ambassador]] for Lunar \u2013 footwear and sandals in two states, [[Andhra Pradesh]] and [[Telangana]].<ref>[http://www.indiaglitz.com/finally-ravi-teja-signs-his-first-commercial-telugu-news-132647.html \"Finally Ravi Teja signs his first commercial IndiaGlitz Retrieved 15.05.2015\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150516000047/http://www.indiaglitz.com/finally-ravi-teja-signs-his-first-commercial-telugu-news-132647.html |date=16 May 2015 }}. Indiaglitz.com (13 May 2015). Retrieved on 26 July 2016.</ref> He later endorsed the liquor brand Lord & Master.<ref>[http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/star-hero-to-endorse-a-liquor-brand.html \"Star hero to endorse a liquor brand\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150611003235/http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/star-hero-to-endorse-a-liquor-brand.html |date=11 June 2015 }}. 123telugu.com. Retrieved on 26 July 2016.</ref><ref>[http://www.indiaglitz.com/ravi-teja-to-endorse-lord-and-master-brandy-telugu-news-134988.html \"Ravi Teja endorses Lord & Master\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150612080720/http://www.indiaglitz.com/ravi-teja-to-endorse-lord-and-master-brandy-telugu-news-134988.html |date=12 June 2015 }}. Indiaglitz.com (10 June 2015). Retrieved on 26 July 2016.</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{{Main|Ravi Teja filmography}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Indian film actors]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*{{Facebook|itsraviteja}}\n* {{IMDb name|id= 0712433|name=Ravi Teja }}\n* {{Rotten-tomatoes-person| ravi_teja|Ravi Teja }}\n\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n\n{{Nandi Award for Best Actor}}\n{{NandiSpecialJuryAward}}\n\n{{Authority control}